# Data Dictionary — funk2017 (IO₂, no executable code)

Original: U.S. utility patents 1977–2005 (NBER + Patent Network Dataverse).
Provided sample: raw_data/sciscinet_sample.parquet — 40,000 SCIENTIFIC PAPERS (DATA-SUB: papers stand in for patents; the CD-index formula is identical).

| column | type | meaning |
|--------|------|---------|
| paper_id | str | focal paper id |
| year | int | publication year |
| reference_count | int | # predecessors cited |
| citation_count_5y | float | # forward citations within 5 yr (I5) |
| disruption_score | float | precomputed CD5 index, range ~[-1,1]; mean≈0.07, SD≈0.23 in paper |
| author_count | int | # inventors |

CDt index (Eq. 1): CD5 = (n1 - n3)/n where n1=future-cites-focal-not-predecessors, n3=cites-both. The provided disruption_score IS this CD5 (precomputed).
mCD5 = impact-weighted variant (weight = forward citations of the citing paper).
